sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM passengers
WHERE survived = 1 AND sex = 0;

SELECT p.name 
FROM passengers p
WHERE p.sex = 1 AND p.pclass = 1;

SELECT AVG(fare) AS average_fare
FROM passengers
WHERE sex = 0 AND pclass = 1;

external_knowledge:
1st class refers to the highest class of travel, implying a higher fare; 
The query assumes that there is only one ticket per passenger; 
Fare is a measure of the cost of traveling and is used to rank passengers; 
Cumulative fare is a running total of fares, used to provide context to the individual fares.

